title: An Ideal Husband (1985) BBC TV
description:
I'm having trouble gathering information about this movie.
It is an Oscar Wilde play.
This version was presented on TV by the BBC as part of a four-part mimi-series.
I think the date of this show was 1985. 
I think this because this video is on the DVD along with Lady Windermenre's Fan,
which is clearly listed on IMDb as 1985.

All I can be sure of is theat Jeremy Brett plays the part of Lord Goring.
Susan Hampshire plays the part of his fiance.
Jeremy Brett later becomes Sherlock Holmes.
Susan Hampshire came to prominence in 1971 in Forsyte Saga.
I'm sorry not to know more about this movie.

At any rate I think it is the best of all the versions of An Ideal Husband.
